Class AccountDatabase

java.lang.Object
AccountDatabase
public class AccountDatabase extends Object
Manages a database of accounts. Provides methods to add, remove, find, and print Also manages an archive of closed accounts.
Author:
Ricardo Pina

      Parameters:
      accountNumber - the account number to find

    • findAccountsByProfile

      public Account[] findAccountsByProfile(Profile profile)
      Returns the accounts associated to a given profile.
      Parameters:
      profile - the account number to find
      Returns:
      an array of accounts associated to the profile or an empty array if no matches are found

    • withdraw

      public boolean withdraw(AccountNumber number, double amount)
      Withdraws a given amount from an account. If the account is a money market account and the balance falls below $2000 the account is downgraded to a savings account.
      Parameters:
      amount - the amount to withdraw
      accountNumber - the account number to withdraw from
      Returns:
      true if the withdrawal was successful, false otherwise

    • deposit

      public void deposit(AccountNumber number, double amount)
      Deposits a specified amount into an account.
      Parameters:
      number - The account number of the account to deposit into.
      amount - The amount to deposit.

    • printArchive

      public void printArchive()
      Prints the archive of closed accounts. If the database is empty, prints a message indicating that.

    • printByBranch

      public void printByBranch()
      Prints all accounts in the database, ordered by branch location (county, city). If the database is empty, prints a message indicating that.

    • printByHolder

      public void printByHolder()
      Prints all accounts in the database, ordered by account holder and account number.

    • printByType

      public void printByType()
      Prints all accounts in the database, ordered by account type and account number. If the database is empty, prints a message indicating that.

    • printAllAccounts

      public void printAllAccounts()
      Prints all accounts in the database. If the database is empty, prints a message indicating that.

    • hasAccountOfType

      public boolean hasAccountOfType(Profile profile, AccountType type)
      Checks if a profile already has an account of a specific type.
      Parameters:
      profile - The profile to check.
      type - The account type to check.
      Returns:
      True if the profile has an account of the specified type, false otherwise.
